Meow is a young woman roaming the streets and nightclubs of Tel Aviv. She lives in empty apartments and surfs internet chat rooms. She decides to meet Alex, her chat buddy. They plan to meet in a nightclub but a suicide bombing prevents their meeting. She survives the attack and after she finds Alex comatose in hospital she moves into his empty apartment. Gradually, the tenants start referring to her as Alex and she assumes his identity.
